  "title": "Head of Operations",
  "description": "<p>The firm is a small boutique asset management firm founded by a former CEO of a major financial institution. We are a holder of a Capital Markets Services Licence regulated by the Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS) and manage investment funds in a VCC structure as well as segregated accounts, investing mainly in publicly traded equities, fixed income securities.</p><p>The Role:</p><p>We are seeking an experienced and dynamic Head of Operations and Compliance to manage our operations and compliance functions.</p><p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>•\tFund Operations & Oversight: Oversee all daily fund operations, including trade settlement, FX funding, and daily position/cash reconciliations with custodian banks.</p><p>•\tNAV & Reporting: Review monthly NAV packs from fund administrators and draft NAV reports for managed accounts, ensuring accuracy and timeliness.</p><p>•\tCompliance Management: Conduct pre-trade and post-trade compliance reviews and strengthen overall fund tax compliance.</p><p>•\tFund Structuring & Projects: Lead complex fund projects, including the launch, migration, and restructuring of funds under the MAS VCC framework.</p><p>•\tTechnology Implementation: Manage and optimize key financial systems; experience with Microsoft Access is highly valued.</p><p>•\tRegulatory Compliance</p><p>•\tKnowledge with ABSS and Payroll system</p><p>•\tHandling annual audit of the Investment Funds and the company’s financial accounts.</p><p>The Ideal Candidate:</p><p>•\tHolds a bachelor’s or master’s degree in finance, Accounting, or a related field. A CPA or equivalent professional qualification would be an advantage.</p><p>•\tHas 10+ or more years of experience in fund operations and compliance within the asset management industry.</p><p>•\tPossesses a proven track record of success in:</p><p>o\tLaunching or migrating funds using the Singapore VCC framework.</p><p>o\tManaging the full operational lifecycle of investment funds.</p><p>o\tNavigating regulatory requirements with MAS.</p><p>•\tDemonstrates in-depth knowledge of financial products and the asset management landscape.</p><p>•\tIs proficient with professional financial tools such as Bloomberg, Microsoft Access, and fund accounting systems.</p><p>•\tExhibits strong leadership skills, is highly independent, results-oriented, and meticulous.</p><p>•\tIs an effective communicator</p><p></p>",
